cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach for simultaneous training of multiple tasks using reinforcement learning. It also uses neural networks for learning the compound policy. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as the proposed approach is tested on complex robotic systems. 

Additionally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses reinforcement learning for learning multiple tasks. 

It may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with controlling robotic systems. 

Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves learning tasks related to reachability of end effectors.
